        <abstract>
            <p>Sends observations inspired by reading CD’s works.</p>
            <p>Animal showing teeth an indication of pleasure, connected with sexual instinct.</p>
            <p>Infant feet will curl around an object placed on the sole, indicating a primitive prehensile function.</p>
            <p>Effects of climate on man’s physical countenance evidenced in similarity of N. American Indians and Yankees.</p>
        </abstract>
